i\n* Neeralgi\n* Nivalakhed\n* Othihal\n* Padaganur\n* Puradal\n* Ramanahalli\n* Rampur P.A\n* Rampur P.T\n* Sasabal\n* Saladahalli\n{{col-break}}\n* Shambewad\n* Shirasgi\n* Somajal\n* Somapur\n* Sungathan\n* Surgihalli\n* Tarapur\n* Tavarkhed\n* Thontapur\n* Tilagul\n* Tirupatinagar\n* Turkangeri\n* Uchitnavadgi\n* Vibhutihalli\n* Wanakihal\n* Wandal\n* Warkanhalli\n* Yalgod\n* Yankanchi\n* Yargal B.K\n{{col-break}}\n* Yargal K.D\n* Benakotgi\n* ChikkaKokatnur\n* Shakapur\n* Ingalgi\n{{col-end}}Hangaragi\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Bijapur Fort]]\n\n==References==\n\n* {{EB1911|wstitle=Bijapur}}\n* '''\"Samanya Mahiti\"'''a periodical released by the Bijapur Zilla Parishad.\n{{reflist}}\nhttps://www.facebook.com/pages/Bijapur-Beauty/286380871418949\n\n==Bibliography==\n*{{cite book|title=The Sufis of Bijapur, 1300-1700: Social Roles of Sufis in Medieval India|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=j2F9BgAAQBAJ|first=Richard Maxwell|last=Eaton|publisher=Princeton University Press|year=2015|ref=harv|isbn = 9781400868155}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Commons category|Bijapur district}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090221153702/http://bijapuronline.com/ Tourist information of Bijapur and places nearby]\n* [http://www.bijapurinfo.com/ A Complete Information Portal of Bijapur]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20071009051341/http://www.leadersindia.com/karnataka.html Profiles of all the Districts in Karnataka]\n* [http://bijapur.nic.in/ Bijapur District]\n* [http://www.tribuneindia.com/2002/20020324/spectrum/heritage.htm Bijapur Heritage]\n* [http://www.kamat.com/kalranga/bijapur/adilshah2.htm Profile of Adil Shah II.]\n* [http://www.ioc.u-tokyo.ac.jp/~islamarc/WebPage1/htm_eng/bijapur-eng.htm Bijapur at the Islamic Monuments of India Photographic Database]\n* [http://www.alhashmi.org/ SUFIS OF BIJAPUR]\n* [http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/article2428099.ece IGNOU in the hindu newspaper]\n{{Clear}}\n\n{{Settlements in Bijapur district}}\n{{Karna