 10|10]]\n| [[Rodolfo Massi]]\n| style=\"background:#FFEB64;\" rowspan=\"5\"|[[Jan Ullrich]]\n| style=\"background:#FFA8A4;\" rowspan=\"8\"|[[Rodolfo Massi]]\n| style=\"background:#E4B3AB;\"|[[C\u00e9dric Vasseur]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Prologue to Stage 11#Stage 11|11]]\n| [[Marco Pantani]]\n| style=\"background:#E4B3AB;\"|[[Roland Meier]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Stage 12 to Stage 21#Stage 12|12]]\n| [[Tom Steels]]\n| style=\"background:#E4B3AB;\" | [[Laurent Jalabert]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Stage 12 to Stage 21#Stage 13|13]]\n| [[Daniele Nardello]]\n| style=\"background:#E4B3AB;\" | [[Andrea Tafi (cyclist)|Andrea Tafi]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Stage 12 to Stage 21#Stage 14|14]]\n| [[Stuart O'Grady]]\n| style=\"background:#E4B3AB;\" | [[Giuseppe Calcaterra]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Stage 12 to Stage 21#Stage 15|15]]\n| [[Marco Pantani]]\n| style=\"background:#FFEB64;\" rowspan=\"7\"|[[Marco Pantani]]\n| style=\"background:#E4B3AB;\"|[[Christophe Rinero]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Stage 12 to Stage 21#Stage 16|16]]\n| [[Jan Ullrich]]\n| style=\"background:#E4B3AB;\" | [[St\u00e9phane Heulot]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Stage 12 to Stage 21#Stage 17|17]]\n| \u2014{{efn|name=\"note-stage-17\"}}\n| \u2014{{efn|name=\"note-stage-17\"}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Stage 12 to Stage 21#Stage 18|18]]\n| [[Tom Steels]]\n| style=\"background:#FFA8A4;\" rowspan=\"4\" | [[Christophe Rinero]]\n| style=\"background:#E4B3AB;\" | [[Christophe Mengin]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Stage 12 to Stage 21#Stage 19|19]]\n| [[Magnus B\u00e4ckstedt]]\n| style=\"background:#E4B3AB;\"| [[Jacky Durand]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Stage 12 to Stage 21#Stage 20|20]]\n| [[Jan Ullrich]]\n| ''no award''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[1998 Tour de France, Stage 12 to Stage 21#Stage 21|21]]\n| [[Tom Steels]]\n| style=\"background:#E4B3AB;\"| [[Pascal Chanteur]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\"| Final\n! style=\"background:#FFDB00;\" |[[Marco Pantani]]\n! style=\"background:#46E800;\" | [[Erik Zabel]]\n! style=\"background:#FF3E33;\" | {{font color|white|Christophe Rinero|link=yes}}\n! [[Jan Ullrich]]\n! {{ct|COF|1998}}\n! style=\"background:#E42A19;\" colspan=\"2\" | {{font color|white|Jacky Durand|link=yes}}\n|}\n\n*In stage one, [[Abraham Olano]], who was second in the points classification, wore the green jersey, because first placed [[Chris Boardman]] wore the yellow jersey as leader of the general classification.<ref>{{cite web|title=Stage 1: Dublin \u2013 Dublin (180,5 km): Overall standings|url=http://www.letour.com/98us/etapes/01/classements/itg.html|website=[[Tour de France]]|publisher=[[Amaury Sport Organisation]]|accessdate=24 March 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20001025183839/http://www.letour.com/98us/etapes/01/classements/itg.html|archivedate=25 October 2000}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Stage 1: Dublin \u2013 Dublin (180,5 km): Overall sprinters|url=http://www.letour.com/98us/etapes/01/classements/ipg.html|website=[[Tour de France]]|publisher=[[Amaury Sport Organisation]]|accessdate=24 March 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20001025174137/http://www.letour.com/98us/etapes/01/classements/ipg.html|archivedate=25 October 2000}}</ref>\n\n==Final standings==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\" | Legend\n|-\n| [[File:Jersey yellow.svg|20px|link=General classification in the Tour de France|alt=A yellow jersey.]]\n| Denotes the winner of the [[General classification in the Tour de France|general classification]]\n| [[File:Jersey green.svg|20px|link=Points classification in the Tour de France|alt=A green jersey.]]\n| Denotes the winner of the [[Points classification in the Tour de France|points classification]]\n|-\n| [[File:Jersey polkadot.svg|20px|link=Mountains classification in the Tour de France|alt=A white jersey 